profile_positions.description:
Senior E-Commerce Solution Architect, worked as consultant for HomeChoice (PTY) LTD.
One of South Africa's largest online retailers, headquarter in Cape Town, and they are a omni-channel homeware and household textiles retailer.

- I have an important role guiding client's integration, testers and business analysts team in order to enable clients to introduce a cloud based solution in their IT architecture and designing the migration plan towards a cloud infrastructure and platform;
- Proposing enhancements of the existing architecture and business process to improve the efficiency of a procedure and/or simplify the application development/maintenance;
- Producing enterprise architecture models and documents, business case, business glossary, vision, business requirements and other relevant documents;
- Strong customer facing interaction. Participation in technical working groups, progress meetings and meetings with the clients and other partners;
- Responsible for setup, prepare and administer Oracle Commerce Cloud;

- Lead teams on architecture and integration standards, conventions, and optimisations. Responsible for analysis of the Integration of different information systems defining architectural solutions for interoperability.

- Responsible for identify requirements with Business Analysts and offer solution following best practises in E-Commerce for Multi-Site, Catalogs, Products, Search, Promotions, Customers (Shoppers), Inventory, Payment, Orders, E-mails, Webhooks, Web APIs, Server Side Extensions and more;

- Responsible for migration plan and data migration, systems integration, internationalisation (i18n), mapping payloads between legacy system and E-Commerce Platform;

- Responsible for setup Storefront Single Sign-On (SSO) customer logins integration and guide partners in order to enable integration with an external customer data store or identity management tool (Idp) using SAML 2.0;

- Extensive use of RESTful APIs and payloads in JSON format.

