Senior E-Commerce Technical Consultant for HomeChoice (PTY) LTD.
- Responsible for setup, prepare and administer Oracle Commerce Cloud;
- Responsible for analysis of the Integration of different information systems defining architectural solutions for interoperability for Multi-Site, Catalogs, Products, Promotions, Customers (Shoppers), Inventory, Payment, Orders, E-mails, Webhooks, Web APIs and more;
- Responsible for identify requirements with Business Analysts and offer solution following best practises in Oracle Commerce Cloud;

- Responsible for client's catalog definition and setup, customer's journey in storefront, search configuration and optimisation, payments and payment gateway integration flow, migration plan and data migration, systems integration, internationalisation (i18n), mapping payloads between legacy system and Oracle Commerce Cloud;

- Responsible for setup Storefront Single Sign-On (SSO) customer logins integration with an external customer data store or identity management tool using SAML 2.0;

- Extensive use of RESTful APIs and OAuth 2.0 security framework for data exchange with JWT and payloads in JSON format.

Working with the JEE architecture and E-Commerce using Oracle Commerce Platform (Oracle ATG Web Commerce + Oracle Endeca Commerce + Oracle Commerce Business Intelligence) and Oracle Commerce Cloud;

- Experience across a number of different business models, such as B2C, B2B, my responsibility is that understand new features and improvements to clients leveraging all benefits and best practices of Oracle Commerce Platform;

- Leading E-Commerce Solutions area for Oracle Commerce Platform, identifying and implementing continuous improvements to the business and working as Java ATG + Endeca Architect;

- Responsible for sizing, architectural and technical issues, business process and systems integration on projects based on ATG Web Commerce and Endeca Web Commerce;

- Responsible for elaborate proposal and estimate effort for new projects together with commercial team;

